    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-01-18T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-01-18T13:00:00-05:00" n="44"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d44">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72119/8710: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wallace</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-01-18T18:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 18, 1920, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received 10.23 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>179. Mission. The Supreme Council meets tomorrow morning, Monday, probably for
                    the last time as Lloyd George returns to England Tuesday and Clemenceau will
                    presumably retire to the country. Expect Committee of Ambassadors will handle
                    unfinished business.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wallace</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
